The paper discusses embeddings, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. The focus is on the dimensionality of embeddings for sparse features and data, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category, as the paper discusses embeddings in the context of machine learning tasks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely, as embeddings are used in many AI applications, such as natural language processing and computer vision. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible sub-category, as embeddings are often used to represent images and other visual data. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also possible, as embeddings are commonly used in natural language processing tasks. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper discusses measuring dimensionality in terms of information entropy.
